Version 0.5.5
- Added options --sdrel for SDCC linker .rel format and --trs for TRS-80 CMD format.
- Inserted entry address in the hex format end record.
- Fixed filename in AMSDOS header.
- Added support for IFDEF and IFNDEF directives.

Version 0.5.4.beta2
- Added third pass option and automatic switch to it on phase errors.

Version 0.5.4.beta1
- Phase error detection.
- Added debug build option.

Version 0.5.3
- Fixed bug where several errors returned exit status 0.

Version 0.5.2
- Added warning when the 64KB limit is crossed.
- All warnings now display line information.

Version 0.5.1
- Enhanced REPT syntax with control variable, initial value, and increment.
- Macro parameters are now expanded inside REPT and IRP.
- Added new ## operator and .SHIFT directive for use inside macros.
- Added --bin command-line option to explicitly select raw binary mode.
- Public symbol listing can now be generated alongside the complete listing.

Version 0.5.0
- Added new directives .ERROR and .WARNING.
- Added new operators HIGH, LOW, !, &&, ||, and conditional expressions.
- Added synonyms for existing operators: &, |, =, ~, !=, <, >, <=, >=, <<, >>.
- Brackets [] can now be used for indirection, with optional bracket-only mode.
- Added support for embedded '$' in number formats.
- Identifiers with '$' are stripped after checking reserved words.
- Added options to generate 8086 code from Z80 sources.
- Added support for .tzx and .cdt tape images with or without a BASIC loader.

Version 0.4.0
- Fixed debug messages for autolocal blocks being shown without debug options.
- PROC and LOCAL now work in autolocal mode.
- Added command-line options -v, -E, and --equ.
- Added DEFINED operator.
- Fixed bug in nested IF blocks causing unbalanced ENDIF errors.

Version 0.3.7
- Added --alocal option for autolocal mode.

Version 0.3.6
- Added -I option.
- Fixed bug in TAP checksum code.
- Added --nocase option for case-insensitive operation.

Version 0.3.5
- Added -err option to send error messages to standard output.

Version 0.3.4
- Added support for undocumented SLL instruction.

Version 0.3.3
- Some undocumented Z80 instructions are now accepted (see undoc.asm).

Version 0.3.2
- Improved clarity of some error messages.
- Fixed $ operator to evaluate the beginning of the current instruction.
- Added % operator (same as MOD).

Version 0.3.1
- Added new output format --tapbas.
- Fixed issues with * and / token handling.

Version 0.3.0
- Fixed dependencies.
- Added support for numbers with & prefix.
- Fixed bugs in LD A and LD simple instructions.
- Added directives: DEFL, MACRO, REPT, IRP, ENDM, EXITM.
- Improved error handling for unbalanced PROC blocks.

Version 0.2.4
- Added directives: LOCAL, PROC, ENDP (see local.asm for examples).

Version 0.2.3
- Added MSX output format.
- Binary numbers now accept % prefix.
- Added operators EQ, LT, LE, GT, GE, and NE.

Version 0.2.2
- Improved debug output control.

Version 0.2.1
- Fixed incorrect line number display for errors.
- Added INCBIN directive for binary file inclusion.
- File names can now be quoted with single or double quotes.

Version 0.2.0
- Added .tap object format and --name option.

Version 0.1.1
- Added support for negative offsets in (ix + offset) or (iy + offset).

Version 0.1.0
- Added PRL format code generation for CP/M Plus RSX.
